#   URI-001: Unify branch/commit naming machinery

*Status: DONE ‚Äî all 5 stages LANDED / CONFIRMED.*  Branch-vs-commit-hash
disambiguation WAS scattered across `dog` /
`keeper` / `sniff` / `graf`, each re-deriving ref structure from the string
heuristically; the canonical resolved form was unsettled (the DIS-025
pin-in-query shape fought ULOG dedup ‚Äî see "Canonical form" below); and hash
length was hardcoded to 40 (sha1), so nothing was sha256 ready.  This ticket
unified all of it behind one keeper-owned rule: `DOGRefSplitPin` is gone,
`DOGIsHashlet`-as-disambiguator is replaced by branch-first `GRAFRefIsName` /
`KEEPResolveRef`, and the `len==40` recognizers route through `DOGIsFullSha`.

##  The one rule
Disambiguation lives *only in keeper*, is *branch-first*, and is
*hash-length-agnostic*:

 1. Does the ref name a *branch* (REFS lookup)?  ‚Üí branch / trunk.
 2. Else, is the ref *all hex* AND does that *hash exist* (pack index)?
    ‚Üí hashlet (detached).  The index knows sha1 (40) vs sha256 (64); callers
    never test a length.
 3. Else ‚Üí not found.

*Remote exception:* a ref requested *from* a peer (`ssh:`/`be:`) is NOT
disambiguated locally ‚Äî the raw ref is sent and the remote keeper resolves it.

