##  Canonical form (revised 2026-06-07, LANDED `b2b4ff9e`)
The earlier DIS-025 plan put the resolved hash in a query *pin*
(`?/<proj>/<branch>/<sha>`, detached `?/<proj>//<sha>`).  It collides twice:
ULOG dedup keys on the row text *before `#`* (so the tip sha must stay in the
REFS *fragment* ‚Äî every tip-move of one ref shares a dedup key, `dog/ULOG.c:663`),
and in argv URIs the fragment is already *verb payload* (PATCH squash/merge/
rebase mode, GET `#~N`/`#sha`).  So the funnel canonicalises the *SCOPE only*
and NEVER pins a tip into query or fragment:

  - `?/<proj>`             ‚Äî trunk scope.
  - `?/<proj>/<branch>`    ‚Äî branch scope (may nest).
  - `?/<proj>/<full-sha>`  ‚Äî DETACHED: a bare commit, no branch (branch-first:
                            the segment is a branch, else the commit).

The resolved sha pin lives ONLY in `--at` (`<root>?/<proj>/<branch>#<sha>`,
read from the wtlog) and REFS storage (`?heads/main#<sha>`, UNCHANGED ‚Äî keeps
ULOG dedup intact).  Downstream dogs re-resolve the scope to a tip themselves
(`KEEPResolveRef`), so the argv fragment stays free for the verb.

Decisions (2026-06-07): (1) `--at`'s fragment is ALWAYS the resolved sha,
NEVER a commit message; the message is a query-less `#msg` URI (or `-m`).
(2) A future fragment-locator (`?/<proj>/<branch>#<hashlet|msg>` selecting a
SPECIFIC commit in scope, unifying sha / hashlet / message-search) is DEFERRED
‚Äî today the fragment is left as verb payload.

ZERO on-disk churn: resolver/emitter change only.

